author: Richard Kim
title: Humphreys community supports displaced service members [Image 1 of 3]
text:
Air Force Master Sgt. Paul Alfred, 607th Combat Weather Squadron flight chief, talks to displaced Soldiers and Airmen, Dec. 29, about different resources and activities available to them during the weekend such as the Humphreys Better Opportunities for Single Soldiers (BOSS) program. Recently 320 service members were displaced due to maintenance issues. The U.S. Army Garrison Humphreys community provided supplies, Dec. 29, to those service members. (U.S. Army Photo by Richard Kim)
